# Code Style Guidelines

## TypeScript

- Use TypeScript with strict mode (Deno default)
- Always include proper TypeScript types
- Use type inference when types are obvious
- Export types from centralized type files when shared

## Component Patterns

- Prefer functional components
- Use async/await over promises
- Maximum function length: 50 lines
- Maximum file length: 300 lines
- One component per file
- Keep components small and focused (single responsibility)

## Naming Conventions

- Routes: kebab-case (e.g., `user-profile.tsx`)
- Islands: PascalCase (e.g., `Counter.tsx`, `UserProfile.tsx`)
- Components: PascalCase (e.g., `Button.tsx`, `Layout.tsx`)
- Utilities: camelCase (e.g., `formatDate.ts`, `validateEmail.ts`)
- Types/Interfaces: PascalCase (e.g., `UserData`, `ApiResponse`)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (e.g., `API_BASE_URL`)

## Import Patterns

- Use `@/` path alias for project root imports (configured in `deno.json`)
- Use relative imports when importing from nearby files
- Group imports: external packages, then internal imports
- Use JSR imports when available: `jsr:@scope/package`

## Error Handling

- Implement proper error handling in all code
- Use try-catch blocks for async operations
- Provide meaningful error messages
- Handle edge cases appropriately

## Documentation

- Add JSDoc comments for complex functions
- Document public APIs and interfaces
- Include parameter and return type documentation
- Explain non-obvious logic with comments
